+## 2026-06-21 (claude/hex-color-chart-branding-svusth) — branding: hex input + color chart + 3 save slots [PUSHED]
+
+- **What:** `app/project/[id]/workspace/BrandingBlock.tsx` — added a "Brand colors" section to the Brand pill popover. Live preview swatch + a hex text input (loose-hex `normalizeHex`: accepts `abc`/`#ABC`/`001122` → `#rrggbb`) + native `<input type=color>` + a 20-swatch **color chart** grid you click to pick. Three **save slots** below — clicking "Save" drops the current draft color into a slot; clicking a filled slot loads it back into the picker; `×` clears it.
+- **Persistence (zero backend change):** slots write into the free-form `projects.branding` blob under `primary_color` / `accent_color` / `saved_color_3`. The first two are the canonical keys `brand-theme.ts:extractBrandTheme` already reads, so saved colors actually theme deliverables. `brandingForDigest` ignores the extra keys (key-allowlisted); global `/api/user/brand` PATCH still only writes the 4 agent fields by design, so colors persist at project level.
+- **Gates:** `tsc --noEmit` exit 0 · eslint exit 0 (deps installed via `bun install`). No new deps. No tests existed for BrandingBlock.
